<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-638-928  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 638 928.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 16 1990 n309 p2(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rights Advocate. (Mitchell Kapor; Newsmaker) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jackson, Kelly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mitchell Kapor has formed the Electronic Frontier Foundation toserve as an organization to protect the rights of computer usersand to educate the public about technology.andP;  The new organizationwill fund litigation to protect computer users' first amendmentrights and will attempt to quell public fears and misconceptionsabout technology.andP;  Kapor claims that the recent anti-computercrime crusade has violated users' rights of free speech and hasresulted in unfair searches and seizures of computers.andP;  Thefoundation will also funnel resources to teach technology to thepublic and to policy makers.andP;  Funding for the foundation came fromKapor, Steve Wozniak and an unidentified high-technology pioneer.andO;Each donated hundreds of thousands of dollars.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer CrimesComputer HackersPublic RelationsRightsUser GroupsElectronic Frontier FoundationPoliticsLegal Issues.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Mitchell Kapor. (portrait)Person:    Kapor, Mitchell (political activity).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>